# farmer_livelihood_model

This directory contains the code and data required to run the farmer
livelihood model for Hamirpur, Jalaun, Sitapur and Sultanpur districts
in northern India.

## code

### model.cpp
The model itself, written in Rcpp (C++)

### model.R
R script which calls the model

### run_scenarios.R
R script which runs the various scenarios for each district. This is
the main script which calls all others. It should be run from the root
directory (i.e. from wrr_paper/) and is the only script which should be
run by the user. Individual scenarios can be run by commenting out
those that are not required. 

### plots.R
R script to make plots from the model output

### code/config
Directory containing the config scripts for each district/scenario
combination. Each district also has a file specifying the model
parameters (*_params.R), which do not vary between scenarios, and
two files containing irrigation schedules
(*_bau|policy_irrigation_schedule.R).

## data

### input
directory containing all input data

### output
Directory containing all output data, in RData or txt format

### plots
Directory containing all plots for WRR paper

